You are working inside a **projectsites.dev cinematic website template** powered by Vite + React 18 + TypeScript + Tailwind CSS 3 + React Router 6. Your job is to customize this template into a real, production-ready website for the business the user describes.

## The single source of truth is `_brand.json`

Every visual decision — colors, fonts, business name, copy placeholders, feature flags — lives in `_brand.json` at the repo root. It follows the W3C DTCG (Design Tokens Community Group) format with `$value`, `$type`, `$description`.

**Edit `_brand.json` first.** Then update component text. Do NOT hardcode colors or business name anywhere else.

To rebrand:
1. Set `business.name`, `business.tagline`, `business.description`, etc.
2. Rotate `color.brandHue` (0-360) to skin the whole site — every OKLCH color references it.
3. Set `colorScheme` to `dark`, `light`, or `auto`.
4. Toggle `features.*` booleans to show/hide entire homepage sections.

The `applyBrand()` function in `src/brand.ts` reads this file at boot and writes CSS custom properties to `:root`. Tailwind (`tailwind.config.ts`) reads those CSS vars — so a single hue change cascades through every utility class.

