## Customization checklist (do these every time)

1. **Edit `_brand.json`** with the real business data. Rotate `color.brandHue` for visual variety.
2. **Replace `{PLACEHOLDER}` strings** in `src/pages/*.tsx` with real copy.
3. **Update `index.html`** title + meta description + canonical + OG image URL.
4. **Update `public/site.webmanifest`** name + short_name + description.
5. **Update `public/robots.txt`, `public/sitemap.xml`, `public/llms.txt`** with the real domain.
6. **Toggle `features.*` in `_brand.json`** — disable sections that don't fit the business (e.g. set `pricing: false` for a portfolio, `team: true` for an agency).
7. **Add real images.** Drop into `public/` and reference with `/path.jpg`. Set `loading="eager"` + `fetchPriority="high"` only on the LCP image.
8. **Run `npm install` then `npm run build`** to verify everything compiles.

## Hard rules

- **Never delete `_brand.json` or `src/brand.ts`** — the whole theme system depends on them.
- **Never hardcode hex colors** in components. Use Tailwind tokens (`bg-accent`, `text-text-muted`) which resolve from CSS vars.
- **Never use `npm i pkg`** — add deps to `package.json` and let `npm install` resolve them.
- **All images need `alt` text.** No exceptions. Empty `alt=""` only for decorative images.
- **Every clickable email/phone/address must be a real link** (`mailto:`, `tel:`, Google Maps URL).
- **Press `⌘K` (or `Ctrl+K`) opens the command palette.** Mounted in `Layout.tsx`. Do not remove.
- **Reduced motion is respected automatically** via `@media (prefers-reduced-motion: reduce)`.

## Stack constraints (WebContainer)

- Use libsql/sqlite if you need a database (not better-sqlite3 — no native binaries).
- Prefer Node scripts over shell scripts.
- Do not run `npm run dev` as a shell command — bolt.diy starts the dev server.
